<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Functions: predefined functions - index</title>
</head>

<body>

    {{index .Words 2}}
    {{index .Words 0}}
    {{index .Words 1}}
    {{.Lname}}

    <!-- 
        index
        a func you can use in a template
        it is a "predefined global function"

        index returns the result of indexing its first argument by the following arguments.
        thus "index x 1 2 3" is, in Go syntax, x[1][2][3]. Each indexed item must be a map,
        slice, or array
     -->

    <!-- FYI -->
    This is a go template comment
    {{/*(index .Wisdom 3).Name*/}}

</body>

</html>